<h3>Research &gt; Online Resources for Youth &gt; Books &amp; Authors</h3>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul class="resource_list">
<li><a href="https://www.pilkey.com/"><strong>Dav Pilkey</strong></a> &ndash; Dav&rsquo;s extra crunchy website o&rsquo; fun.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.eric-carle.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Eric  Carle</strong></a> &ndash; Eric Carle has written and  illustrated dozens of books for young children, the most famous being 1969's<em> The  Very Hungry Caterpillar</em>. Includes a listing of all of Carle&rsquo;s books, a  video gallery and upcoming events at his museum.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.janbrett.com" target="_blank"><strong>Jan Brett</strong></a> &ndash; Official site of the author/artist of <em>The Mitten</em> and other  children's favorites. Includes free coloring pages and fun projects to make.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.fancynancyworld.com/#/home/"><strong>Jane  O'Connor</strong></a> &ndash; Explore, Play and  Party with Fancy Nancy activities.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.jsworldwide.com/"><strong>Jon Scieszka Worldwide</strong></a> &ndash; Latest news about the author and his  books.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.marypopeosborne.com" target="_blank"><strong>Mary Pope  Osborne</strong></a> &ndash; The website maintained by Mary Pope  Osborne, author of the &quot;Magic Tree House&quot; series of children's books.  Contains research guides and newsletters by the author.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.libraryaware.com/1074/Subscribers/Subscribe" target="_blank"><strong>NextReads</strong></a> &ndash; Sign up for <em>NextReads</em>,  a free e-mail newsletter about Picture books, Kid's Books (grades 4-8) and  Young Adult Books (High school readers).</li>
<li><a href="https://rpa.warrenville.com:80/rpa/default/webauth.htm?rs=novelistk8plus" target="_blank"><strong>Novelist  K-8Plus</strong></a> &ndash; Contains materials for all K-8 grade levels and includes picture books,  children's &quot;chapter&quot; books and young adult titles. The <em>NoveList</em> Learning Center helps teachers meet the reading needs of their students. <strong>This  database is available  remotely with your Warrenville Library card number and 4 digit PIN. </strong></li>
<li><a href="https://www.ronroy.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Ron Roy</strong></a> &ndash; Ron Roy has written many mystery books  for children, including the popular &quot;A to Z Mysteries&quot; series, and  the new series, &quot;Capital Mysteries.&quot; Site includes games and trivia.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.roalddahl.com/"><strong>Roald Dahl</strong></a> &ndash; Welcome to the world of Roald Dahl,  author of <em>Charlie and the Chocolate Factory</em>, <em>James and the Giant  Peach</em>, and <em>BFG</em>.</li>
<li><a href="https://rosemarywells.com/?page_id=800"><strong>Rosemary  Wells</strong></a> &ndash; Read and play with  the little bunnies, Max and Ruby.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.whatshouldireadnext.com/"><strong>What  Should I Read Next?</strong></a> &ndash; Enter a book title that you enjoyed  and the site will recommend titles to try next.</li>
</ul>
